column3: Q2: What permission did you have, as of June 2021
column4: Q3: Did you receive free access to Github Copilot for your role as a top open source maintainer on June 21, 2022? You can check current eligibility at this link: https://github.com/github-copilot/free_signup
column5: Q4: Do you use copilot (either because you received free access, or because you purchased it?)

column4: I have access to Github Copilot because I work for Microsoft
Don't remember. I'm eligible now because my org bought me a seat. Never used it.
I think I had signed up for Copilot. The first email I have about trying it out was received October 22, 2021
yes,  but not from the project refererred to in the email
Received earlier access from a friend on the team at the time
I would never use CoPilot, even if I had free access
I don't care about Github Copilot, and do not see the point in using it.
Unaware that free access for maintainers existed!
